You are working on a Shopify app for Bloqio CRO.

Project rules:
- Never edit multiple unrelated files in one change.
- Always inspect current files before proposing fixes.
- For Liquid, never use parentheses around filters inside {{ }}.
- Assign first, then apply filters.
- Respect Shopify schema validation constraints.
- Never leave blank defaults in schema settings where Shopify rejects them.
- Prefer select instead of range when there are only two options.
- Do not duplicate JS initialization.
- Keep app embed logic separate from app block logic.
- Preserve merchant theme compatibility.
- Do not invent files, settings, schema keys, or assets.
- Explain exactly which file is being edited and why.
- Prefer minimal, reversible changes.
- Never refactor unrelated code while fixing a bug.
- Before changing code, identify the likely root cause.